<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1059.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                        Great Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-19">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Foreign office remains firm in its intention to discourage as far as
                                possible the new £10,000,000 loan and does not intend to acknowledge
                                the note from the Chinese Legation announcing signature to this
                                loan.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>